http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Jamia-Nooriyya-meet-begins/article13985687.ece

The 53rd anniversary celebrations of Jamia Nooriyya Arabic College began at Pattikkad, near Perinthalmanna. on Wednesday.Jamia Nooriyya president Sayed Hyderali Shihab Thangal hoisted the festival flag in the afternoon.Inaugurating the meet, Indonesian Islamic scholar Mohammed Ilham Rahmatulla Swalih said that cleansing of the mind and giving emphasis on humanism were the signs of excellence in scholarly pursuit.Jamia secretary Syed Sadikali Shihab Thangal presided over the fucntion. Scholar K. Mammad Faisi, Abdurahman Randathani, MLA, N. Shamsuddin, MLA, and Calicut University Registrar T.A. Abdul Majeed spoke.A meeting of Jamia Nooriyya old students heralded the meet. Samastha Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama vice president A.P. Mohammed Musliar Kumaramputhur led a mass ziyarat.Nalakath Soopy, former Minister for Education, will inaugurate a State-level competition of Dars students on Thursday morning. Scholar P. Kunhani Musliar will inaugurate a Khateeb conference. E.T. Mohammed Basheer, MP, will inaugurate an award session in the afternoon.Minister for Home Ramesh Chennithala will inaugurate a peace conference on Friday morning. Syed Basheerali Shihab Thangal will preside over the function. Minister for Tourism A.P. Anil Kumar and social critic Sebastian Paul will be guests.